TITLE: Extending Components with Styled-Components
DESCRIPTION: Pattern for extending a base component with margins while maintaining the principle that components should not define their own outside margins. Parent components should add margins to components they render.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sharetribe/flex-docs/blob/master/docs/coding-conventions.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// P.js
//
const P = styled.p`
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 24px;
`;
export default P;

// SomeComponent.js
//

// Create a version of P with margins added
const Paragraph = styled(P)`
  margin: 24px 0;
`;

const SomeComponent = props => {
  return (
    <div {...props}>
      <Paragraph>Some text content.</Paragraph>
      {/* ... */}
    </div
  );
};
```

