TITLE: EDN Format Example
DESCRIPTION: Example showing the syntax and structure of EDN format used in process definitions
SOURCE: https://github.com/sharetribe/flex-docs/blob/master/src/docs/howto-transaction-process/edit-transaction-process-with-flex-cli/index.md#2025-04-18_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: clojure
CODE:
```
;; This is a comment. Comments in edn start with ";;"
;;

{:number 1 ;; a number, for example `1`, `2.2`, `-500`, `1.23456M`
           ;; (where `M` denotes that exact precision is desired)
 :string "This is a string"
 :boolean true ;; or false
 :keyword :this-is-a-keyword
 :namespaced-keyword :namespaced/keyword
 :vector [1, "abc", false] ;; same as "array" in JSON
 :map {:first-name "John",
       :last-name "Doe",
       :age 55} ;; same as "object" in JSON
}
```

